HEADWORD: Strisores
<hw>Stri*so"res</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.; cf.
L. <ets>stridere</ets> to creak, whiz, buzz.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of passerine birds including the humming birds, swifts,
and goatsuckers. It is now generally considered an artificial
group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

